For designers, every asset has a name, and that should also be true for the metaverse. Currently most people are familiar with every NFT having an id number, but that should soon be replaced with a name. ENS can be that open source permissionless system for virtual goods.

My vision for helping to bring about this vision, is to focus on the utility eco system for ENS domains, bringing in new users base on new use cases, including using ENS domains as creative NFTs for designers and artists. I think the ENS will also be necessary for the metaverse

My vision for ENS, is that it will become one of the pillars of Web3, providing a single naming and ownership layer and including all types of naming system including all types of data, e.g. profiles, files, smart contracts, locations, machine ids, real estate . . .

My background is in the arts and tech, including working as a digital sculptor and 3D designer in NYC for over a decade. I have also always been into the software and the web, including running a web design business, writing my own 3D design software package.

Please consider voting for me for a steward position for Public Goods/Community ENS DAO working groups. I have been working nearly every day to support the ENS community for more than six months. ENS üöÄüöÄ https://t.co/a9syxvCuFD
